Methods¶

Data source, time frame, geographic scope and collection methods ¶

The data for this analysis is the results from beach-litter surveys conducted in Switzerland from !! Put your dates here !! through January 18, 2021.

All surveys that were conducted on Bielersee, Neuenburgersee, Thunersee, Walensee, Zurichsee, Lac Lman, Brienzersee and Lago Magiore were considered.

The data was collected according to the protocol described here https://www.plagespropres.ch/. In brief all visible data is collected along a beach within a measured distance from the waters edge. The width of the survey area depends on the terrain and the water level. The visible strand line or the nearest physical structure defines the width of a survey.

Surveys were conducted by the following organizations:

  1. hammerdirt
  2. Association pour le Sauvegarde du leman
  3. Solid Waste Management Ecole Polytechnique Federal
  4. Ecole International de Geneve
  5. Precious plastic leman
  6. Why isn't your association here?

This analysis is an open source document. The working note book is available in the repository located here https://github.com/hammerdirt-analyst/iqals.

Scope of surveys¶

The scope of the surveys includes the total population levels and land use configuration for the adjacent municipality. Land use is quantified by calculating the m of space attributed to buildings wtihin 500m of the survey location and the total length in meters of roads within 1000m of the survey location*.

The results and survey locations can be classified according to the following attributes:

  1. M of buildings within 500m of the survey
  2. Total length of streets/roads within 1000m of the survey
  3. Number of river/canal intersections within 1500m of the survey
  4. Population of the surounding municipality

*Values are calculated using https://shop.swisstopo.admin.ch/en/products/landscape/tlm3D

Franais

Le champ d'application des enqutes comprend les niveaux de population totale et la configuration de l'utilisation des sols pour la municipalit environante. L'utilisation des sols est quantifie en calculant la superficie en m attribue aux btiments dans un rayon de 500 m du lieu de l'enqute et la longueur totale en mtres des routes dans un rayon de 1000 m du lieu de l'enqute*.

Les rsultats et les lieux d'enqute peuvent tre classs selon les attributs suivants :

  1. M de surface au sol des btiments situs dans un rayon de 500m du lieu d'enqute
  2. Longueur totale des rues/routes dans un rayon de 1000 m de l'enqute
  3. Nombre d'intersections de rivires/canaux dans un rayon de 1500m de l'tude
  4. Population de la commune environnante

Les valeurs sont calcules en utilisant https://shop.swisstopo.admin.ch/en/products/landscape/tlm3D

Definition of significant values¶

Significant values are those survey values that are equal to or exceed the 90th percentile of all survey results for the defined code.

(table 3, fig 4).

The chance of finding AT LEAST one G95 for every 10 meters of survey nationally is: ~22.8

The chance of finding AT LEAST one G95 for every 10 meters of survey on Lac Lman is: ~58.1%
